expert%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20weak%20response%20to%20Ukraine's%20assault%20into%20Russian%20territory%20is%20partly%20due%20to%20a%20persistent%20flaw%20in%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20leadership%2C%20a%20warfare%20expert%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-sweden-kursk-incursion-shows-how-hollow-russian-war-machine-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunched%20a%20surprise%20attack%20on%20Russia's%20Kursk%20region%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20early%20August%20and%2C%20by%20late%20September%2C%20said%20it%20controlled%20more%20than%20500%20square%20miles.%20Russia%20has%20not%20taken%20any%20significant%20swathe%20of%20territory%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Bohnert%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20RAND%20Corporation%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20with%20the%20way%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20responded%2C%20not%20even%20appointing%20a%20general%20to%20take%20charge%20of%20what%20is%20clearly%20a%20military%20situation%20rather%20than%20a%20domestic%20security%20matter%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%2C%20I%20think%2C%20an%20element%20of%20he%20doesn't%20want%20to%20make%20anything%20where%20any%20general%20could%20claim%20credit%20for%20being%20the%20victor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20response%20to%20Ukraine's%20attack%20has%20not%20been%20highly%20effective.%20Ukrainian%20troops%20said%20they%20were%20first%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-soldier-russia-troops-kursk-kids-mandatory-service-wsj-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eable%20to%20cross%20into%20Kursk%20easily%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they%20then%20made%20rapid%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20Ukraine's%20progress%20has%20dramatically%20slowed%20as%20Russia%20has%20stiffened%20its%20resistance%2C%20Russia%20has%20only%20been%20able%20to%20take%20back%20some%20villages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20response%20to%20Ukraine's%20attack%20on%20Russian%20soil%20was%20decidedly%20slow.%20Putin%20initially%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2F08%2F18%2Fvladimir-putin-kursk-crisis-reponse%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efroze%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20he%20has%20in%20other%20crises%2C%20but%20Moscow%20eventually%20put%20the%20FSB%20%E2%80%94%20Russia's%20primary%20security%20and%20intelligence%20agency%20%E2%80%94%20in%20charge%2C%20leading%20a%20host%20of%20other%20groups.%20War%20experts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-messy-response-ukraine-kursk-shows-weaknesses-still-plaguing-army-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20BI%20that%20it%20was%20a%20surprising%20move%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20showed%20Russia%20had%20not%20fixed%20long-standing%20issues%20with%20command%20and%20control.%20And%2C%20Bohnert%20said%2C%20those%20security%20forces%20are%20%26quot%3Bsubordinate%20to%20Putin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c00c66f6-4166-464f-a2fc-270dc15b4b6b%5C%22%3EPutin%20in%20charge%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20president%20has%20played%20an%20unusually%20direct%20role%20in%20leading%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20at%20times%20giving%20orders%20himself.%20US%20intelligence%20said%20in%202022%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-giving-orders-generals-ukraine-battlefield-dysfunction-grows-us-intelligence-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPutin%20was%20giving%20orders%20directly%20to%20his%20generals%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20that%20that%20was%20causing%20confusion%20for%20his%20military%20leadership.%20This%20isn't%20how%20political%20leaders%20typically%20handle%20military%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBohnert%20said%20Putin%20not%20wanting%20to%20give%20generals%20credit%20fit%20with%20his%20behavior%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethroughout%20his%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20began%20in%20February%202022.%20%26quot%3BDictators%20don't%20like%20anyone%20coming%20around%20that%20looks%20like%20the%20next%20strong%20man%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Putin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66bf1eea1aa2ac29ee31ca56%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20meets%20top%20military%20officials%20in%20the%20Kremlin.%3Cp%3EGAVRIIL%20GRIGOROV%20via%20Getty%20Images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20logic%20could%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20start%20of%20Russia's%20invasion%20when%20Russia%20failed%20to%20quickly%20seize%20all%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20instead%20was%20forced%20to%20fight%20in%20the%20east%2C%20Bohnert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20invasion%2C%20there%20were%20multiple%20military%20officials%20in%20charge%20of%20different%20sectors%20%26quot%3Band%20there%20was%20no%20coordination%20other%20than%20Putin.%20What%20people%20don't%20realize%20is%20that%20was%20by%20design.%20Because%20it's%20very%20clear%20Putin%20never%20wanted%20to%20give%20any%20general%20credit%20for%20winning%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20officials%20told%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20that%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20invasion%2C%20there%20was%20no%20central%20war%20commander%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20decisions%20were%20instead%20made%20from%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeeks%20after%20the%20start%20of%20the%20full-scale%20invasion%2C%20Russia%20put%20Gen.%20Aleksandr%20V.%20Dvornikov%20in%20charge%20of%20operations%20in%20Ukraine.%20He%20was%20fired%20from%20the%20role%20weeks%20later%2C%20with%20the%20UK%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20saying%20it%20was%20highly%20likely%20because%20of%20the%20military's%20%26quot%3Bpoor%20performance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20top%20Russian%20generals%20have%20been%20arrested%20during%20this%20war%20on%20various%20charges%2C%20including%20accepting%20bribes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutin's%20motives%20for%20these%20arrests%20are%20unconfirmed.%20But%20The%20Moscow%20Times%20reported%20in%20May%20that%20the%20FSB%20was%20going%20after%20them%20with%20the%20Kremlin's%20approval%20so%20that%20blame%20could%20be%20assigned%20for%20Russia's%20invasion%20going%20badly%20and%20to%20take%20control%20of%20the%20Russian%20army's%20huge%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225040%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Destroyed%20Russian%20military%20vehicles%20in%20a%20field.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d7456a14a5cd1fcc8cbb94%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDestroyed%20Russian%20military%20vehicles%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Sudzha%2C%20in%20the%20Kursk%20region%2C%20in%20August.%3Cp%3EKIRILL%20CHUBOTIN%2FUkrinform%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESimon%20Sebag%20Montefiore%2C%20a%20historian%20and%20author%20on%20Russian%20history%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2023%2F07%2F19%2Fputin-wagner-prigozhin-russia-history-mercenaries-fear-strong-generals%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Foreign%20Policy%20last%20year%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20failure%20to%20promote%20an%20effective%20general%20to%20fight%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20is%20one%20of%20Putin's%20most%20egregious%20lapses.%20Indeed%2C%20one%20of%20the%20chief%20duties%20of%20the%20war%20leader%20is%20to%20select%20generals%20who%20can%20win%20victories%20and%20remove%20those%20who%20can't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20%26quot%3BPutin%20has%20either%20never%20found%20that%20talented%20general%2C%20or%20more%20likely%2C%20so%20fears%20the%20threat%20of%20one%20that%20he%20has%20preferred%20stalemate%20to%20the%20peril%20of%20a%20victory%20won%20by%20someone%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cc99203e-fb14-4efa-87eb-c1d7acec2a63%5C%22%3EA%20broken%20culture%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20have%20said%20that%20Putin's%20choices%20often%20do%20not%20make%20sense%20from%20a%20military%20perspective%20and%20instead%20seem%20focused%20on%20preserving%20his%20political%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeorge%20Barros%2C%20a%20Russia%20analyst%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%20think%20tank%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20%26quot%3BPutin%20at%20every%20junction%20now%20continues%20to%20do%20what%20is%20politically%20expedient%20and%20militarily%20stupid%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20not%20pursuing%20another%20full-scale%20mobilization%20of%20troops%20or%20declaring%20a%20move%20like%20martial%20law%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20Kursk%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20in%20Russian%20politics%20have%20said%20that%20the%20firings%20of%20Russian%20officials%20are%20intended%20to%20send%20a%20message%20about%20the%20risks%20of%20consolidating%20too%20much%20power.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fputin-sends-russias-defense-minister-warning-shot-1893964%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20Newsweek%20in%20April%20that%20the%20arrest%20of%20the%20deputy%20defense%20minister%20earlier%20this%20year%20might%20have%20been%20meant%20as%20a%20warning%20to%20then-defense%20minister%20Sergei%20Shoigu%20about%20becoming%20too%20powerful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pattern%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20authoritarian%20regimes%20like%20Putin's%20more%20generally%2C%20Bohnert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20for%20military%20officials%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat's%20a%20fact%20of%20any%20sort%20of%20authoritarian%20or%20totalitarian%20regime%2C%20where%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20look%20too%20capable.%20You%20always%20want%20to%20be%20mediocre%20if%20you're%20n