644-f39e-4e2b-a0a0-a17ab77d6b7b%5C%22%3EWe%20met%20up%20at%20the%20'divorce%20bench'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20started%20with%20James.%20He%20was%20a%20straight%20guy%20in%20my%20office%20who'd%20gone%20through%20a%20terrible%20divorce.%20I%20didn't%20know%20him%20then%2C%20but%20desperate%20for%20help%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-advice-for-amicable-easy-simple-divorce-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easked%20him%20for%20some%20advice%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20that's%20how%20I%20was%20introduced%20to%20an%20unofficial%20club%20%E2%80%94%20the%20straight%20guys'%20divorce%20club.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20from%20all%20over%20the%20company%2C%20from%20the%20mailroom%20to%20the%20C-suite.%20Our%20group%20had%20men%20from%20every%20ethnicity%2C%20four%20different%20religions%2C%20multiple%20generations%2C%20and%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20political%20divide.%20There%20were%20American-born%20men%20and%20immigrants%20like%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20group%2C%20we%20would%20meet%20informally%20at%20the%20%26quot%3Bdivorce%20bench%26quot%3B%20just%20outside%20the%20office%2C%20which%20was%20actually%20just%20the%20smoker's%20bench%2C%20to%20exchange%20info%2C%20tactics%2C%20and%20divorce%20updates.%20After%20a%20while%20of%20getting%20to%20know%20each%20other%2C%20we%20began%20to%20talk%20even%20more%20openly%20and%20fearlessly.%20I%20got%20advice%20on%20how%20to%20best%20work%20with%20lawyers%2C%20how%20to%20act%20at%20the%20office%2C%20how%20to%20handle%20the%20feelings%20of%20rage%20and%20loss%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0basically%2C%20how%20to%20get%20through%20this%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b4def1d4-87a1-48ea-ace1-4f95d3e8f295%5C%22%3EDivorce%20became%20the%20great%20equalizer%2C%20and%20surviving%20it%20was%20our%20common%20goal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20shared%20and%20listened%20deeply%20to%20each%20other%2C%20our%20diversity%20of%20experiences%20and%20thinking%20seemed%20to%20power%20us.%20In%20this%20DEI%20microcosm%20of%20up%20to%20eight%20men%20depending%20on%20the%20day%2C%20we%20didn't%20agree%20on%20everything.%20Many%20of%20us%20might%20have%20canceled%20each%20other%20in%20another%2C%20still-married%20life.%20I%20certainly%20had%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-dei-expert-helped-startup-founder-canary-culture-equitable-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifficult%20talks%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20more%20conservatively%20religious%20guys%20about%20my%20gayness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20here's%20the%20thing%3A%20We%20were%20imperfect%20allies%2C%20and%20that%20was%20okay.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20could%20only%20talk%20to%20each%20other%20using%20the%20reference%20points%20we%20had%20from%20our%20individual%20lives%2C%20so%20our%20questions%20were%20often%20clunky%2C%20ill-informed%2C%20and%20sometimes%20even%20offensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-programs-america-diversity-equity-inclusion-pushback-how-to-fix-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20gold%20of%20DEI%3C%2Fa%3E%20lies.%20In%20this%20group%2C%20only%20people%20who%20were%20complete%20outsiders%20to%20each%20other%20could%20see%20each%20other%20so%20clearly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d33fd217-d268-439c-b7e9-5f9ff7a5f2da%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20power%20of%20being%20unlikely%20allies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20divorcing%20guy%2C%20who'd%20never%20had%20a%20gay%20friend%20in%20his%20life%2C%20wanted%20to%20know%20if%20he%20could%20ask%20me%20%26quot%3Babout%20some%20gay%20stuff.%26quot%3B%20Nothing%20was%20off%20the%20table%20in%20our%20group%2C%20so%20I%20said%20yes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20asked%20how%20we%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0my%20ex-partner%20and%20I%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0had%20decided%20who%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20man%26quot%3B%20and%20who%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20woman%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%2C%20in%20my%20opin