%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20made%20dietary%20changes%20to%20lower%20his%20blood%20pressure%2C%20which%20he%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUnusually%2C%20these%20changes%20didn't%20include%20reducing%20his%20salt%20intake.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20he%20was%20about%20to%20ski%20down%20a%20mountain%20in%202012%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupplements-top-nutrition-scientist-gut-expert-takes-ditched-tim-spector-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETim%20Spector%3C%2Fa%3E%20started%20seeing%20double.%20The%20epidemiologist%20and%20nutrition%20scientist%20made%20it%20down%20safely%2C%20but%20he%20later%20discovered%20he'd%20had%20a%20mini-stroke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpector%20was%2053%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20considerably%20younger%20than%2074%2C%20the%20average%20age%20that%20people%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20where%20he%20is%20from%2C%20have%20strokes%2C%20according%20to%20a%202021%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Stroke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3-ways-to-prevent-strokes-doctor-cases-rise-young-people-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrokes%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20seen%20as%20a%20condition%20affecting%20mostly%20older%20people%2C%20more%20younger%20people%20are%20having%20them.%20The%20prevalence%20of%20strokes%20in%20adults%20aged%2018%20to%2044%20increased%20by%2014.6%25%20between%202011%20to%202013%20and%202020%20to%202022%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20stroke%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESpector%2C%20who%20is%20also%20the%20cofounder%20of%20the%20science%20and%20nutrition%20company%20ZOE%2C%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fhypertension%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20blood%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20common%20after%20a%20stroke%20because%20most%20people%20who%20have%20one%20also%20have%20high%20blood%20pressure%2C%20according%20to%20the%20American%20Heart%20Association.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpector%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%20the%20two%20things%20he%20did%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-lower-blood-pressure-heart-attack-risk-stroke-cardiologist-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower%20his%20blood%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20his%20stroke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f05fc786-d9d7-49a2-8939-99687abeb5ff%5C%22%3ESpector%20switched%20to%20a%20salt%20alternative%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPatients%20with%20high%20blood%20pressure%20are%20commonly%20told%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flower-blood-pressure-cut-back-on-salt-super-effective-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereduce%20the%20amount%20of%20salt%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20eat.%20This%20is%20partly%20because%20salt%20increases%20the%20amount%20of%20water%20the%20body%20retains%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20increases%20the%20pressure%20in%20the%20blood%20vessels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Spector%20said%20he%20struggled%20with%20eating%20%26quot%3Btasteless%20food%26quot%3B%20when%20he%20cut%20out%20salt.%20And%2C%20it%20didn't%20seem%20to%20have%20any%20impact%20on%20his%20blood%20pressure%2C%20because%20Spector%20is%20%26quot%3Bsalt-resistant.%26quot%3B%20That%20means%20eating%20salt%20doesn't%20hugely%20affect%20his%20blood%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20he%20ate%20more%20potassium%2C%20which%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Ftools%2Felena%2Finterventions%2Fpotassium-cvd-adults%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecommends%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20reduce%20high%20blood%20pressure%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eby%20using%20a%20salt%20alternative%20made%20from%20potassium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20levels%20of%20sodium%20and%20potassium%20in%20the%20body%20affect%20each%20other%2C%20the%20more%20potassium%20you%20eat%2C%20the%20more%20sodium%20is%20lost%20though%20the%20urine%2C%20according%20to%20the%20AHA.%20Potassium%20can%20also%20help%20the%20walls%20of%20blood%20vessels%20relax%2C%20easing%20the%20pressure%20inside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a9e73f44-e573-405a-a4cf-46a7aa9607e3%5C%22%3EHe%20ate%20more%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESpector%20was%20already%20eating%20a%20minimal%20amount%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-people-make-cutting-down-ultra-processed-foods-dietitian-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultra-processed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20also%20something%20stroke%20patients%20are%20typically%20advised%20to%20do.%20So%20to%20further%20improve%20his%20diet%2C%20he%20%3Cem%3Eadded%3C%2Fem%3E%20healthy%20foods%20%E2%80%94%20fruit%20and%20vegetables%20to%20be%20exact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEating%20more%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%20was%20linked%20to%20a%20lower%20risk%20of%20high%20blood%20pressure%20in%20a%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10349693%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereview%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20studies%20published%20in%20the%20European%20Journal%20of%20Nutrition.%20Researchers%20suggested%20this%20could%20be%20because%20they%20contain%20lots%20of%20potassium%2C%20or%20because%20eating%20plenty%20of%20fruit%20and%20vegetables%20is%20also%20associated%20with%20a%20lower%20risk%20of%20obesity%2C%20which%20is%20a%20risk%20factor%20for%20high%20blood%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20still%20aren't%20sure%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-foods-lower-blood-pressure%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efoods%20are%20best%20for%20lowering%20blood%20pressure%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20British%20Heart%20Foundation%20recommends%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%20that%20are%20high%20in%20nitrates%2C%20such%20as%20beetroot%2C%20sp