t%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flazy-girl-job-trend-tiktok-explained-defending-low-stress-work-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elazy%20girl%20jobs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Move%20fast%20and%20break%20things%3F%20No%20cap%2C%20that's%20sus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20zoomers%20aren't%20to%20blame%20for%20their%20lack%20of%20progress%20in%20Silicon%20Valley.%20Gen%20Z%20founders%20and%20would-be%20founders%20are%20stepping%20into%20a%20vastly%20different%20tech%20world%20from%20that%20of%20their%20predecessors%20%E2%80%94%20a%20world%20where%20launching%20a%20unicorn%20is%20far%20more%20difficult%2C%20and%20publicly%20scrutinized%2C%20than%20it%20was%20for%20the%20garage-band%20generation%20of%20Jobs%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates-still-pulling-strings-microsoft-ai-copilot-chatgpt-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGates%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20that%20has%20prompted%20many%20Gen%20Zers%20to%20question%20whether%20they%20even%20want%20to%20strive%20for%20that%20level%20of%20world-conquering%20superstardom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounders%20%26quot%3Bare%20as%20zealous%20and%20as%20smart%20as%20they%20were%2020%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jerry%20Neumann%2C%20a%20venture%20capitalist%20and%20adjunct%20professor%20at%20Columbia%20University.%20It's%20the%20tech%20industry%20itself%20that%20isn't%20evolving%20as%20rapidly%20as%20it%20once%20did.%20When%20millennials%20were%20young%2C%20the%20internet%20was%20new%2C%20nearly%20lawless%2C%20and%20ripe%20not%20necessarily%20for%20disruption%20but%20for%20defining.%20Then%20came%20the%20iPhone%2C%20a%20technological%20advance%20that%20changed%20society%2C%20making%20ideas%20like%20Uber%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdating-apps-find-love-romance-online-tinder-match-total-scam-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBumble%3C%2Fa%3E%20possible.%20Gen%20Z%20is%20coming%20of%20age%20in%20an%20era%20when%20the%20same%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20are%20diffuse%20and%20dominant.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20just%20not%20that%20same%20technological%20opportunity%20to%20build%20big%20companies%20fast%2C%26quot%3B%20Neumann%20said.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20millennial%20founders%20ran%20so%20that%20Gen%20Z%20founders%20could%20walk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20young%20founders%20are%20mostly%20left%20to%20work%20on%20incremental%20technological%20innovations%20in%20a%20mature%20market%2C%20which%20are%20often%20bought%20up%20by%20the%20bigger%20companies%20well%20before%20their%20founders%20become%20household%20names.%20That%20may%20mark%20a%20successful%20startup%20exit%20but%20not%20a%20path%20to%20fame.%20%26quot%3BIn%20order%20to%20be%20the%20next%20Zuckerberg%20or%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20a%20disruptor%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kimberly%20Eddleston%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20entrepreneurship%20and%20innovation%20at%20Northeastern%20University.%20These%20big-name%20founders%20%26quot%3Beither%20disrupted%20an%20industry%20or%20created%20a%20brand-new%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20As%20the%20tech%20industry's%20biggest%20companies%20have%20maintained%20their%20hold%2C%20they've%20acquired%20competitors%20and%20new%20technologies.%20Even%20if%20Facebook%20doesn't%20carry%20the%20same%20cache%20of%20cool%20as%20it%20did%20in%202009%2C%20nearly%20half%20of%20humanity%20still%20uses%20Meta's%20various%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20acquired%20%E2%80%94%20products%2C%20like%20Instagram%20and%20WhatsApp%2C%20without%20any%20clear%20upstart%20challengers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEntrepreneurial%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20also%20facing%20a%20tougher%20road%20to%20funding.%20Gone%20are%20the%20days%20of%20walking%20into%20Thiel's%20office%20in%20a%20hoodie%20and%20watching%20him%20make%20it%20rain.%20From%20the%20final%20quarter%20of%202021%20to%20the%20final%20quarter%20of%202023%2C%20venture-capital%20investment%20plummeted%20from%20%2452.8%20billion%20to%20%2410.6%20billion%2C%20the%20lowest%20of%20any%20quarter%20since%202019.%20Rising%20interest%20rates%2C%20paired%20with%20the%20cautionary%20tales%20of%20the%20likes%20of%20Adam%20Neumann%20and%20Holmes%2C%20have%20increased%20scrutiny.%20Though%20that%20makes%20the%20barrier%20to%20entry%20for%20a%20tech%20startup%20higher%2C%20perhaps%20the%20ideas%20that%20survive%20it%20will%20be%20more%20valuable.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20a%20good%20refresh%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alexandra%20Debow%2C%20a%2022-year-old%20who%20dropped%20out%20of%20New%20York%20University%20and%20has%20raised%20pre-seed%20money%20for%20her%20photo-sharing%20social%20app%20Swsh.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20just%20want%20hype.%20People%20want%20true%20value%20behind%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20firms%20are%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-startups-rapid-funding-rounds-2024-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSuddenly%252C%2520it%2527s%2520feeling%2520very%2520%25222021%2CAI%2520firms%252C%2520risking%2520inflated%2520valuations.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexception%20to%20the%20trend%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20investors%20are%20still%20pouring%20money%20into%20them.%20Perhaps%20not%20coincidentally%2C%20that's%20also%20the%20industry%20in%20which%20perhaps%20the%20biggest%20Gen%20Z%20founder%20reigns.%20Alexandr%20Wang%2C%20the%2027-year-old%20who%20cofounded%20Scale%20AI%20in%202016%20when%20dropping%20out%20of%20MIT%2C%20has%20become%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20youngest%20self-made%20billionaires%2C%20with%20a%20net%20worth%20of%20%242%20billion.%20His%20company%20employs%20contractors%20who%20do%20the%20grunt%20work%20of%20labeling%20data%20for%20companies%20to%20train%20machine-learning%20models.%20And%20while%20Wang%20has%20become%20the%20subject%20of%20profiles%20in%20major%20publications%2C%20his%20name%20calls%20up%20little%20recognition%20outside%20the%20tech%20world.%20Scale%20AI%20did%20not%20make%20Wang%20available%20for%20an%20interview%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20vibe%20shift%20among%20younger%20founders%3A%20Some%20are%20less%20interested%20in%20becoming%20massive%20public%20figures%20and%20facing%20the%20backlash%20that%20ultimately%20follows.%20They%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20trail%20of%20destruction%20left%20by%20rapid%20tech%20advances.%20They've%20seen%20a%20smiling%20Zuckerberg%20on%20the%20cover%20of%20Wired%20in%202016%20under%20the%20headline%20%26quot%3BCould%20Facebook%20Save%20Your%20Life%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20they've%20seen%20him%20on%20the%20cover%20again%20just%2015%20months%20later%2C%20his%20face%20bruised%20and%20bloodied%2C%20with%20the%20outlet%20teasing%20a%20feature%20about%20%26quot%3Bhow%20a%20confused%2C%20defensive%20social%20media%20giant%20steered%20itself%20into%20a%20disaster.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20move%20fast%20and%20break%20things%20in%20healthcare%2C%20you%20go%20to%20jail%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ibrahim%20Rashid%2C%2027%2C%20who%20founded%20Strong%20Haulers%2C%20a%20startup%20meant%20to%20help%20people%20manage%20their%20symptoms%20of%20illnesses%20like%20long%20COVID.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20move%20fast%20and%20break%20things%20in%20social%20media%2C%20you%20destroy%20elections.%26quot%3B%20Rashid%20didn't%20set%20out%20to%20be%20a%20founder%2C%20but%20his%20personal%20experience%20with%20long%20COVID%20gave%20him%20the%20idea.%20He%20started%20the%20company%20in%202022%20but%20has%20kept%20working%20in%20sustainable%20investing%20while%20building%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERashid%20said%20he%20closely%20followed%20the%20story%20of%20Holmes%2C%20who%20is%20now%20serving%2011%20years%20in%20prison%20for%20defrauding%20investors%20and%20lying%20about%20the%20ability%20of%20her%20technology%20at%20Theranos%20to%20diagnose%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20diseases%20from%20a%20drop%20of%20blood.%20There's%20also%20Bankman-Fried%20and%20Martin%20Shkreli%2C%20who%20were%20on%20the%20Forbes%2030%20Under%2030%20list.%20Enough%20past%20hotshots%20have%20gone%20on%20to%20ignominy%20that%20the%20list%20has%20come%20to%20be%20known%20as%20cursed%3B%20last%20year%2C%20Forbes%20even%20began%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fforbes-hall-shame-30-under-30-lists-regrets-sbf-ftx-2023-11%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPlenty%2520of%2520people%2520on%2520the%2Cand%2520most%2520are%2520in%2520finance.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHall%20of%20Shame%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20for%20its%20disgraced%20recipients.%20(Rashid%20ultimately%20did%20not%20make%20the%20final%20%26quot%3B30%20Under%2030%26quot%3B%20list%20for%202023%2C%20for%20which%20he%20was%20submitted.)%20When%20Alexis%20Barreyat%2C%20a%20cofounder%20of%20the%20social-media%20app%20BeReal%2C%20was%20named%20to%20Fortune's%20%26quot%3B40%20Under%2040%26quot%3B%20list%20in%202022%20at%2027%2C%20his%20entry%20appeared%20not%20with%20a%20headshot%20but%20a%20blank%20avatar.%20Barreyat%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20emailed%20questions%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20young%20founders%20think%20the%20spotlight%20might%20not%20be%20worth%20the%20scrutiny.%20%26quot%3BWe%20try%20to%20take%20a%20lot%20more%20conservative%20approaches%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Julian%20Kage%2C%20a%2019-year-old%20student%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20who%20founded%20the%20diagnostic%20testing%20startup%20Exactics%20with%20other%20undergrads.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20success%2C%20but%20we%20can%20see%20the%20downfall%20of%20how%20terrible%20being%20famous%20can%20be.%20I%20don't%20think%20we%20feel%20quite%20the%20same%20need%20to%20be%20put%20on%20a%20pedestal.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20he%20said%2C%20his%20startup%20has%20been%20slow%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20press%20and%20social%20media.%20It's%20starting%20to%20make%20content%20for%20social%20media%2C%20like%20educational%20videos.%20But%20Kage%20said%20the%20company%20wanted%20the%20science%20and%20the%20product%20%26quot%3Bto%20speak%20for%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20taking%20on%20the%20role%20of%20talking%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20is%20more%20values-driven%20in%20the%20workplace%20than%20older%20generations.%20In%20a%20Deloitte%20survey%2C%20about%2040%25%20of%20young%20workers%20said%20they'd%20turned%20down%20employers%20that%20didn't%20align%20with%20their%20values%20or%20rejected%20work%20assignments%20they%20found%20unethical%20%E2%80%94%20about%2035%25%20of%20millennials%20said%20the%20same.%20That%20plays%20into%20how%20founders%20think%20about%20their%20companies%20and%20themselves.%20Gen%20Zers%20%26quot%3Bexpect%20you%20to%20be%20more%20casual%20and%20show%20up%20more%20as%20your%20full%20self%2C%26quot%3B%20Debow%20said.%20There's%20little%20division%20between%20a%20Monday-morning%20office%20persona%20and%20a%20Friday-at-the-bar%20persona.%20It's%20partly%20from%20a%20place%20of%20encouraging%20authenticity%2C%20but%20also%20from%20growing%20up%20in%20an%20always-online%2C%20and%20always-watched%2C%20generation%20during%20which%20cancel%20culture%20took%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20investors%20taking%20fewer%20risks%20and%20innovation%20happening%20at%20more%20incremental%20levels%2C%20Eddleston%20said%20the%20path%20to%20megasuccessful%20business%20owner%20seems%20to%20be%20operating%20backward%3B%20instead%20of%20people%20getting%20famous%20for%20their%20ideas%2C%20more%20people%20profit%20off%20their%20fame%20with%20a%20brand%20line.%20Think%3A%20Kylie%20Jenner's%20beauty%20line%20or%20the%20YouTuber%20Emma%20Chamberlain's%20coffee.%20These%20are%20safer%20bets%20for%20investors%2C%20she%20said%2C%20but%20safe%20bets%20could%20pass%20over%20innovation.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20nervous%20we're%20losing%26quot%3B%20the%20pioneering%2C%20American%20individualistic%20persona%2C%20Eddleston%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20we%20won't%20see%20Gen%20Z%20founders%20standing%20before%20a%20crowd%20and%20unveiling%20their%20latest%20shiny%20products%20anytime%20soon.%20But%20the%20young-founder%20era%20was%20likely%20more%20myth%20than%20reality.%20Though%20the%20brash%20Harvard%20dropout%20has%20long%20had%20an%20outsize%20hold%20on%20the%20public%20imagination%2C%20the%20number%20of%20people%20under%2030%20who%20owned%20companies%20in%202015%20(when%20millennials%20solidly%20made%20up%20the%2020-to-30%20age%20cohort)%20had%20dropped%20by%2065%25%20from%20the%201980s.%20Harvard%20Business%20Review%20research%20found%20in%202018%20that%20the%20most%20successful%20founders%20in%20recent%20years%20began%20their%20companies%20at%20an%20average%20age%20of%2045.%20That's%20good%20news%20not%20just%20for%20Gen%20Z%20but%20also%20for%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20the%20oldest%20of%20whom%20turned%2043%20this%20year.%20Success%20could%20still%20be%20on%20the%20horizon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-tech-founder-gap-zuckerberg-bezos-holmes-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728467402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67059ce7198738e3a70f344c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-tech-founder-gap-zuckerberg-bezos-holmes-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Silicon%20Valley%20has%20long%20been%20obsessed%20with%20young%2C%20disruptive%20founders.%20But%20Gen%20Z%20is%20less%20sure%20about%20moving%20fast%20and%20breaking%20things.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)%22%2C%22engagement%22