0%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670644cb198738e3a70f45b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkremlin-says-trump-sent-putin-covid-tests-pandemic-denies-calls-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Kremlin%20seemingly%20confirmed%20reports%20that%20then-President%20Donald%20Trump%20sent%20COVID%20tests%20to%20Vladimir%20Putin%20in%20early%202020%2C%20for%20his%20own%20personal%20use.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tspirlet%40insider.com%20(Thibault%20Spirlet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkremlin-says-trump-sent-putin-covid-tests-pandemic-denies-calls-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Housing%20Ice%20Age%20is%20thawing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20house%20surfacing%20from%20a%20melting%20block%20of%20ice%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670548a4198738e3a70f0616%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ERawf8%2FGetty%2C%20Martin%20Poole%2FGetty%2C%20Feverpitched%2FGetty%2C%20dmainternational%2FGetty%2C%20Yamada%20Taro%2FGetty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20not%20feel%20like%20it%20yet%2C%20but%20the%20housing%20market's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-higher-home-prices-fewer-sales-inventory-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIce%20Age%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20finally%20thawing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWould-be%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20have%20found%20themselves%20stuck%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years.%20For-sale%20signs%20stood%20frozen%20in%20front%20yards%20as%20home%20shoppers%20balked%20at%20prices.%20Wild%20swings%20in%20mortgage%20rates%20discouraged%20almost%20everyone%20from%20venturing%20out%20into%20the%20market.%20Many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-housing-market-mortgage-buying-car-interest-rates-new-jobs-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efelt%20as%20if%20they%20had%20no%20option%20but%20to%20stay%20put%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20when%20I%20talk%20to%20housing%20experts%20these%20days%2C%20they%20speak%20cautiously%20of%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20weather%2C%20a%20warming%20in%20store%20for%20American%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreen%20shoots%20are%20popping%20up%20everywhere.%20The%20typical%20borrowing%20rate%20for%20a%2030-year%20home%20loan%20is%20near%20the%20lowest%20it's%20been%20in%20two%20years%2C%20which%20could%20nudge%20more%20sellers%20to%20emerge%20from%20hibernation.%20The%20pool%20of%20available%20homes%20on%20the%20market%20is%20larger%20than%20at%20any%20point%20since%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20While%20the%20median%20home%20price%20nationwide%20is%20up%20by%203%25%20to%205%25%20compared%20with%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20that's%20actually%20within%20the%20range%20that%20economists%20typically%20look%20for%20in%20a%20well-balanced%20market.%20If%20things%20keep%20trending%20this%20way%2C%20we%20should%20expect%20to%20see%20this%20coming%20spring%2C%20the%20time%20of%20year%20when%20transactions%20typically%20pick%20up%2C%20that%20more%20people%20are%20ready%20to%20get%20moving%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWould%20this%20mean%20we're%20back%20to%20normal%3F%20Definitely%20not.%20Things%20may%20be%20more%20stable%20than%20they%20were%20during%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20home-trading%20frenzy%20or%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20slowdown%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20housing%20market's%20problems%20are%20solved.%20It'll%20be%20hard%20for%20both%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20to%20shake%20off%20the%20pessimism%20of%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20especially%20when%20budgets%20are%20stretched%20so%20thin%20and%20home%20prices%20remain%20so%20high.%20That%20reality%20shouldn't%20obscure%20the%20encouraging%20signals%2C%20though.%20As%20I%20wrote%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenmark-mortgage-rates-lock-in-effect-home-buying-selling-easier-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egummed-up%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Ice%20Age%20I%20was%20talking%20about%20%E2%80%94%20is%20good%20for%20nobody.%20In%20half%20a%20year's%20time%2C%20we%20may%20be%20looking%20at%20a%20healthier%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20tendency%20to%20look%20at%20housing%20in%20binary%20terms%3A%20Is%20it%20a%20better%20time%20to%20be%20a%20seller%20or%20a%20buyer%3F%20But%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20fall%20into%20both%20camps%3B%20most%20sellers%20have%20to%20turn%20around%20and%20purchase%20another%20home%20to%20live%20in.%20Recently%2C%20this%20fact%20of%20life%20has%20created%20what%20Skylar%20Olsen%2C%20Zillow's%20chief%20economist%2C%20calls%20the%20%26quot%3Bmusical%20chairs%26quot%3B%20problem%3A%20People%20can't%20jump%20up%20and%20find%20a%20new%20home%20if%20their%20neighbors%20aren't%20making%20similar%20moves%2C%20so%20everyone's%20stuck%20in%20their%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20reason%20Americans%20find%20themselves%20trapped%20in%20place%20is%20what's%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Block-in%20effect.%26quot%3B%20When%20mortgage%20rates%20hit%20multidecade%20lows%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20millions%20of%20people%20were%20able%20to%20snag%20or%20refinance%20their%20way%20into%20cheaper%20monthly%20costs.%20But%20starting%20in%20the%20spring%20of%202022%2C%20the%20rate%20for%20a%20typical%20mortgage%20soared%2C%20more%20than%20doubling%20from%20those%20pandemic-era%20lows.%20While%20it's%20come%20down%20from%20a%20two-decade%20peak%20last%20October%2C%20the%20prevailing%20loan%20terms%20are%20still%20about%20twice%20as%20expensive%20as%20they%20were%20back%20in%202021%2C%20which%20means%20a%20buyer%20could%20have%20to%20pay%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20more%20each%20month%20toward%20interest%20than%20they%20would%20have%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20want%20to%20give%20up%20a%20good%20deal%2C%20so%20they%20don't%20make%20a%20change%20unless%20they%20absolutely%20have%20to.%20One%20paper%20from%20the%20Federal%20Housing%20Finance%20Agency%20suggested%20that%20the%20lock-in%20effect%20prevented%20a%20whopping%201.3%20million%20home%20sales%20between%20mid-2022%20and%20the%20end%20of%202023.%20A%20mere%202.5%25%20of%20America's%20housing%20stock%20traded%20hands%20in%20the%20first%20eight%20months%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20Redfin%2C%20the%20lowest%20rate%20in%20at%20least%20three%20decades%20and%2031%25%20lower%20than%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20drop%20in%20the%20typical%20rate%20for%20a%2030-year%20loan%20%E2%80%94%20from%20about%207.2%25%20in%20early%20May%20to%206.1%25%20in%20early%20October%20%E2%80%94%20won't%20erase%20the%20lock-in%20effect%2C%20but%20it's%20an%20encouraging%20sign%20for%20buyers%20who%20have%20been%20grasping%20for%20anything%20that%20could%20ease%20the%20burden%20on%20their%20wallets.%20Even%20after%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmortgage-rate-increase-since-federal-reserve-cut-interest-rates-housing-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euptick%20in%20the%20last%20few%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20the%20unexpectedly%20strong%20jobs%20report%2C%20more%20interest-rate%20cuts%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%2C%20which%20signaled%20last%20month%20that%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-rate-cut-explained-inflation-labor-market-conditions-outlook-recession-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturning%20its%20focus%20away%20from%20battling%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20could%20further%20bring%20down%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhow-does-fed-impact-mortgage-rates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethough%20there's%20not%20a%20direct%20connection%20between%20the%20two%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Fannie%20Mae%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20predicts%20the%20rate%20for%20a%20typical%20home%20loan%20could%20end%20next%20year%20at%205.7%25.%20That'd%20be%20within%20spitting%20distance%20of%20what%20the%20experts%20at%20John%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting%2C%20a%20housing-research%20firm%2C%20call%20the%20%26quot%3Bmagic%20mortgage%20rate.%26quot%3B%20Among%20homeowners%20and%20renters%20who%20said%20they%20planned%20to%20use%20a%20mortgage%20to%20purchase%20their%20next%20home%2C%2047%25%20told%20the%20firm%20in%20September%20that%20they'd%20be%20willing%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20a%20rate%20between%205%25%20and%205.49%25.%20Even%20if%20rates%20continue%20their%20downward%20trajectory%2C%20changes%20in%20mortgage%20payments%20typically%20take%20about%20six%20months%20to%20show%20up%20in%20home-sales%20activity%2C%20Ralph%20McLaughlin%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20at%20Realtor.com%2C%20told%20me.%20So%20movement%20now%20could%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20a%20stronger%20uptick%20in%20sales%20next%20spring.%20Fannie%20Mae%20has%20also%20predicted%20that%20the%20total%20number%20of%20sales%20will%20be%20up%20by%2010%25%20in%202025%20compared%20with%20this%20year%2C%20with%20most%20of%20that%20increase%20coming%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22house%20for%20sale%20sign%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e86c31ce7f1785b2e6ba64%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20number%20of%20homes%20being%20listed%20for%20sale%20is%20on%20the%20rise.%20That's%20great%20news%20for%20potential%20buyers.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20mortgage-rate%20movement%20can%20be%20a%20helpful%20guide%20for%20future%20activity%2C%20to%20get%20a%20full%20picture%20of%20what's%20actually%20happening%20in%20the%20real-estate%20market%2C%20you%20need%20to%20look%20at%20two%20data%20points%3A%20inventory%2C%20or%20the%20number%20of%20available%20homes%20on%20the%20market%2C%20and%20new%20listings%2C%20or%20the%20number%20of%20homes%20hitting%20the%20market.%20Olsen%2C%20the%20Zillow%20economist%2C%20likens%20inventory%20to%20a%20swimming%20pool%20and%20new%20listings%20to%20the%20spigot%20that%20keeps%20water%20flowing%20%E2%80%94%20as%20with%20any%20pool%2C%20too%20full%20or%20too%20empty%20is%20a%20problem.%20A%20balanced%20market%20is%20one%20in%20which%20there%20are%20enough%20new%20homes%20to%20meet%20the%20demand%20from%20buyers%2C%20but%20not%20so%20many%20that%20prices%20plummet.%20We're%20still%20a%20long%20way%20from%20refilling%20the%20pool%20of%20homes%20on%20the%20market%3A%20Inventory%20in%20September%20was%20down%20by%20about%2023%25%20from%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%20according%20to%20Realtor.com.%20But%20there%20is%20clear%20improvement%20taking%20place%20here%2C%20too.%20The%20number%20of%20active%20listings%20in%20September%20was%20%3Cem%3Eup%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%2034%25%20from%20the%20same%20month%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20increasing%20to%20its%20highest%20level%20since%20April%202020.%20The%20number%20of%20homes%20newly%20listed%20for%20sale%20in%20September%20was%20also%20up%20by%2011.6%25%20from%20last%20year.%20By%20slowing%20down%20home%20sales%2C%20higher%20rates%20have%20given%20inventory%20time%20to%20build%20back%20up%20from%20pandemic%20lows%20%E2%80%94%20homes%20are%20lingering%20on%20the%20market%20longer%20with%20fewer%20buyers%2C%20so%20the%20pool's%20water%20level%20has%20steadily%20climbed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20homes%20to%20choose%20from%2C%20lower%20mortgage%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20a%20%26quot%3Bpowerful%20combination%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lawrence%20Yun%2C%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors'%20chief%20economist%2C%20adding%20that%20sales%20should%20move%20higher%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20as%20a%20result.%20Buyers%20can%20take%20heart%20in%20another%20data%20point%2C%20which%20is%20that%20far%20fewer%20homes%20are%20being%20snapped%20up%20as%20soon%20as%20they%20hit%20the%20market.%20According%20to%20the%20housing-data%20firm%20Altos%20Research%2C%20there%20were%20about%20half%20as%20many%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20sales%26quot%3B%20in%20late%20September%20as%20there%20were%20in%202022.%20%26quot%3BIt%20looks%20like%20that%20frenzy%20is%20finally%20gone%2C%26quot%3B%20Altos'%20president%2C%20Mike%20Simonsen%2C%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20video%20update.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20baseline%20expectation%20for%20the%20spring%2C%20the%20Redfin%20economist%20Chen%20Zhao%20told%20me%2C%20is%20a%20modest%20uptick%20in%20sales%20and%20new%20listings.%20Most%20economists%20don't%20expect%20mortgage%20rates%20to%20fall%20dramatically%2C%20meaning%20sellers%20will%20slowly%20start%20to%20reenter%20the%20market%20as%20they%20decide%20it's%20time%20to%20make%20a%20change.%20New%20listings%20this%20year%20increased%20by%20about%205%25%20a%20month%20on%20average%20compared%20with%20the%20same%20months%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20you%20might%20expect%20to%20see%20that%20climb%20a%20little%20next%20year%2C%20Zhao%20told%20me%2C%20to%20maybe%2010%25%20year-over-year%20growth.%20The%20total%20number%20of%20homes%20on%20the%20market%20each%20month%20tended%20to%20be%20about%2010%25%20or%2015%25%20higher%20than%20last%20year%2C%20but%20you%20might%20see%20that%20rise%20to%2020%25%20or%2025%25%20when%20you%20compare%202025%20with%20this%20year.%20This%20is%20the%20housing's%20version%20of%20a%20soft%20landing%3B%20there%20won't%20be%20dancing%20in%20the%20streets%2C%20but%20it%20would%20be%20a%20marked%20improvement%20from%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20though%20the%20housing%20market%20is%20recovering%2C%20the%20recovery%20is%20going%20to%20be%20very%20slow%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20going%20to%20see%20anything%20like%20the%20activity%20that%20we%20saw%20in%202021%20or%202020%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%202019%2C%202018%20%E2%80%94%20for%20a%20while.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20if%20buyers%20are%20feeling%20better%20about%20their%20prospects%2C%20that%20should%20grease%20the%20wheels%20of%20America's%20housing%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20note%20that%20forecasts%20are%20just%20forecasts.%20There's%20a%20lot%20that%20could%20change%20in%20the%20next%20year.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-collar-jobs-recession-high-salary-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrength%20of%20the%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20big%20question%20mark%20%E2%80%94%20people%20won't%20move%20if%20they%20don't%20feel%20sure%20about%20their%20next%20paycheck.%20There%20are%20huge%20regional%20differences%20to%20consider%20here%2C%20too.%20Builders%20have%20finished%20a%20lot%20more%20new%20housing%20in%20Sun%20Belt%20states%20in%20the%20lower%20half%20of%20the%20US%2C%20for%20example%2C%20which%20has%20made%20it%20harder%20for%20homeowners%20there%20to%20sell%20at%20their%20desired%20prices%20than%20for%20their%20counterparts%20in%20the%20Midwest%20or%20the%20Northeast.%20Affordability%20is%20still%20a%20huge%20pain%20point.%20An%20August%20survey%20by%20Fannie%20Mae%20suggested%20consumers%20were%20feeling%20remarkably%20optimistic%20about%20the%20future%20of%20mortgage%20rates%2C%20but%20only%2017%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20it%20was%20a%20good%20time%20to%20buy%20a%20home.%20Any%20one%20of%20these%20issues%20could%20chill%20the%20market%20and%20slow%20America's%20exit%20from%20the%20Ice%20Age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20it's%20impossible%20to%20ignore%20the%20signs%20of%20a%20shift%20underway.%20Mortgage%20rates%20are%20a%20key%20piece%20of%20the%20equation.%20I'll%20also%20be%20keeping%20a%20close%20eye%20on%20inventory%20and%20the%20pace%20of%20new%20listings%20hitting%20the%20market%2C%20which%20should%20heat%20back%20up%20starting%20around%20February%20and%20March.%20But%20all%20this%20focus%20on%20the%20numbers%20can%20obscure%20the%20simple%20fact%20that%20people%20have%20to%20move%20for%20all%20kinds%20of%20reasons%20that%20have%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20a%20few%20digits%20and%20a%20percent%20sign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20spoke%20with%20Mark%20Palim%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20Fannie%20Mae%2C%20who%20left%20me%20with%20a%20salient%20piece%20of%20advice%3A%20%26quot%3BLeave%20timing%20the%20bond%20market%20to%20the%20hedge-fund%20guys.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20trying%20to%20predict%20mortgage%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20and%20buying%20or%20selling%20a%20home%20accordingly%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20fool's%20errand.%20Budgets%20matter%2C%20absolutely%2C%20and%20monthly%20payments%20are%20a%20crucial%20consideration%20for%20any%20buyer.%20But%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20should%20remember%20that%20their%20home%20isn't%20just%20an%20investment%20vehicle%20or%20a%20bet%20on%20where%20the%20economy%20is%20headed.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20you%20have%20to%20live%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20sorts%20of%20things%20can%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Palim%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BRates%20may%20move.%20Home%20prices%20may%20go%20up%2C%20home%20prices%20may%20go%20down.%20But%20would%20you%20be%20happy%20living%20there%20for%20a%20while%3F%20Does%20it%20meet%20your%20needs%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-homebuyers-mortgage-rates-spring-real-estate-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22pub