ble-has-to-be-kept-on-a-tight-leash-rbi-124100900317_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Finflation-horse-brought-to-the-stable-has-to-be-kept-on-a-tight-leash-rbi-124100900317_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Remembering%20Nicholas%20Roerich%2C%20The%20Russian%20Who%20Made%20Kullu%20His%20Home%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fab1eejl8_nicholas-roerich_625x300_09_October_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENestled%20amongst%20the%20hills%20of%20Kullu%20in%20Naggar%20is%20a%20gravestone%20with%20these%20words%20on%20it%3A%20%26quot%3BHere%20on%20December%2015%2C%201947%2C%20the%20body%20of%20Maharishi%20Nicholas%20Roerich%20-%20a%20great%20Russian%20friend%20of%20India%20-%20was%20committed%20to%20fire.%20Let%20there%20be%20peace.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20few%20instances%20when%20the%20simplest%20of%20words%20convey%20such%20meaning.%20Nicholas%20Roerich%2C%20who%20was%20born%20on%20this%20day%20150%20years%20ago%2C%20was%2C%20first%20and%20foremost%2C%20an%20Indophile%2C%20someone%20who%20perhaps%20can%20be%20said%20to%20have%20laid%20the%20foundation%20of%20Indo-Russian%20friendship.%20But%2C%20to%20know%20Roerich%20and%20his%20work%20-%20whether%20on%20canvas%20or%20paper%20-%20one%20has%20to%20encounter%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERoerich's%20Time%20At%20Ishwara%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoerich%20was%20a%20painter%2C%20traveller%2C%20writer%2C%20philosopher%2C%20and%2C%20as%20many%20in%20his%20native%20country%20consider%2C%20a%20mystic.%20His%20extraordinary%20life%20is%20the%20stuff%20books%20and%20films%20are%20made%20of%2C%20but%20with%20a%20touch%20of%20the%20sublime%20and%20mystical.%20Roerich's%20abiding%20love%20for%20mountains%20was%20partly%20instrumental%20in%20his%20engagement%20with%20India%20and%20why%20he%20later%20made%20Naggar%20his%20home.%20Early%20in%20life%2C%20his%20family%20spent%20time%20at%20an%20estate%20near%20St.%20Petersburg%20named%20%26quot%3BIshwara%26quot%3B.%20The%20previous%20owner%20had%20hung%20a%20picture%20on%20the%20wall%20of%20what%20Roerich%20later%20realised%20was%20Kanchenjunga.%20As%20a%20child%2C%20he%20loved%20looking%20at%20it.%20Later%2C%20it%20was%20his%20wife%20Elena%20who%20introduced%20him%20to%20Indian%20thought%2C%20especially%20Buddhism%2C%20to%20which%20she%20had%20been%20introduced%20by%20Elena%20Blavatskaya%2C%20one%20of%20the%20founders%20of%20the%20Theosophical%20Society.%20Blavtaskaya%20had%20been%20to%20India%20and%20had%20converted%20to%20Buddhism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Solveigs%20Song%20(1912)%20by%20Nicholas%20Roerich%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Solveigs%20Song%20(1912)%20by%20Nicholas%20Roerich%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fdendk27o_roerich_625x300_09_October_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolveig's%20Song%20(1912)%20by%20Nicholas%20Roerich%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20Roerichs%20Met%20Tagore%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHailing%20from%20an%20upper-middle-class%20family%2C%20Roerich%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20milieu%20where%20his%20family%20often%20entertained%20the%20city's%20cultural%20elites.%20It%20was%20also%20a%20time%20when%2C%20fatigued%20by%20constant%20conflict%20and%20wars%2C%20the%20Western%20world%20was%20increasingly%20looking%20towards%20the%20East%20for%20spiritual%20succour%20to%20%26quot%3Breorient%26quot%3B%20itself.%20At%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20Roerich's%20native%20Russia%20plunged%20into%20revolution%20and%20civil%20war.%20Recuperating%20in%20Finland%20when%20the%20Bolshevik%20Revolution%20gripped%20Russia%2C%20the%20Roerichs%20travelled%20to%20Europe%2C%20never%20to%20return.%20In%20England%2C%20they%20met%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%20and%20were%20greatly%20influenced%20by%20him.%20They%20then%20travelled%20to%20the%20US%2C%20where%2C%20already%20engaging%20with%20Indian%20philosophical%20traditions%2C%20they%20established%20the%20Agni%20Yoga%20Society%20in%20New%20York%20and%20an%20art%20institute.%20As%20we%20understand%20now%2C%20the%20society%20had%20less%20to%20do%20with%20yoga%20and%20was%20more%20focused%20on%20promoting%20religious%20harmony%20and%20the%20brotherhood%20of%20nations%3B%20the%20art%20institute%20went%20on%20to%20become%20the%20Nicholas%20Roerich%20Museum%20in%201949.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20US%2C%20they%20finally%20landed%20in%20India%20in%201923.%20They%20toured%20India%20extensively%2C%20interacted%20with%20its%20cultural%20and%20political%20elites%20and%20civilians%2C%20and%20studied%20its%20ancient%20culture%2C%20traditions%20and%20religions%2C%20all%20of%20which%20found%20expression%20in%20Roerich's%20paintings%20and%20writings.%20It%20was%20from%20India%20that%20Roerich%20embarked%20on%20his%20famed%20Central%20Asian%20expedition%20from%201923-1928%20through%20Sikkim%2C%20Tibet%2C%20Kashmir%2C%20Ladakh%2C%20Siberia%2C%20Altai%20and%20Mongolia.%20But%20the%20mountains%20kept%20beckoning%20to%20him%20and%20he%20finally%20settled%20down%20in%20Naggar%20in%20Kullu.%20There%2C%20he%20founded%20the%20Urusvati%20Himalayan%20Research%20Institute%20in%201928.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Love%20For%20Himalayas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%207%2C000-odd%20paintings%20that%20he%20left%20behind%2C%20at%20least%202%2C000%20are%20dedicated%20to%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20which%20for%20Roerich%20symbolised%20man's%20spiritual%20longing%20and%20spiritual%20transcendence.%20This%20is%20how%20he%20described%20the%20Himalayas%3A%20%26quot%3B.....Here%20was%20the%20Abode%20of%20Rishis.%20Here%20resounded%20the%20sacred%20Flute%20of%20Krishna.%20Here%20thundered%20the%20Blessed%20Gautama.%20Here%20originated%20all%20the%20Vedas.%20Here%20lived%20Pandavas.%20Here%20was%20Gessar%20Khan.%20Here%20was%20Aryavarta.%20Here%20is%20Shambala.%20The%20Himalayas%20are%20the%20Jewel%20of%20India.%20The%20Himalayas%20are%20the%20Treasure%20of%20the%20World.%20The%20Himalayas%20are%20the%20sacred%20symbol%20of%20Ascent.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%5CnMuch%20later%2C%20Roerich%20was%20declared%20a%20National%20Treasure%20Artist%20of%20India%2C%20along%20with%20other%20eight%20masters%20like%20Tagore%2C%20Jamini%20Roy%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Roerichs%20car%20in%20Naggar%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Roerichs%20car%20in%20Naggar%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2F339o8glo_car_625x300_09_October_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoerich's%20car%20in%20Naggar%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20many%20of%20Roerich's%20writings%20have%20an%20Indian%20theme.%20He%20was%20greatly%20influenced%20by%20the%20Hindu%20concept%20of%20the%20cyclical%20nature%20of%20time%2C%20as%20also%20by%20old%20Slavonic%20spirituality%20and%20Russian%20Orthodoxy.%20He%20tried%20to%20promote%20a%20synthesis%20of%20Indian%20and%20Russian%20spirituality.%20Many%20of%20his%20writings%20depict%20the%20struggle%20between%20the%20shadow%20and%20light%2C%20with%20the%20latter%20always%20emerging%20triumphant%20-%20a%20search%20for%20the%20pristine%20%26quot%3BShambala%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDhammapada%20%3C%2Fem%3EIn%20An%20Atheist%20State%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoerich%20was%20not%20alone%20in%20his%20endeavour%20to%20acquaint%20Russia%2C%20or%20the%20world%20for%20that%20matter%2C%20with%20Indian%20spirituality.%20Along%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20his%20sons%20also%20made%20their%20individual%20contributions%20to%20furthering%20Indo-Russian%20friendship%20and%20understanding.%20The%20elder%20son%2C%20George%20(Yuri)%20can%20be%20credited%20with%20promoting%20Indology%20in%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20In%201957%2C%20he%20went%20to%20the%20then-USSR%20and%20lived%20there%20for%20three%20years%2C%20before%20his%20tragic%20untimely%20death.%20Russian%20Indologists%20consider%20him%20and%20his%20contribution%20a%20key%20to%20the%20second%20flowering%20of%20Buddhist%20and%20Indian%20studies%20in%20the%20Soviet%20Union%3B%20the%20first%20occurred%20during%20the%20Tsarist%20period.%20He%20was%20a%20scholar%20who%20championed%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20Russian%20translation%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3EDhammapada%20%3C%2Fem%3E%5BBuddhist%20holy%20text%5D%20by%20Vladimir%20Toporov.%20This%20was%20unheard%20of%20then.%20And%20given%20that%20the%20state%20then%20officially%20denounced%20religion%2C%20this%20was%20a%20revolutionary%20step.%20Later%2C%20the%20writings%20of%20both%20Roerich%20and%20Elena%20helped%20spread%20Indian%20mysticism%20in%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20later%20in%20the%20Russian%20Federation%2C%20with%20a%20number%20of%20Roerich%20Societies%20springing%20up%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Shelkar%20Dzong%20(1928)%2C%20by%20Nicholas%20Roerich%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Shelkar%20Dzong%20(1928)%2C%20by%20Nicholas%20Roerich%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fv6fcq938_roerich_625x300_09_October_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShelkar%20Dzong%20(1928)%2C%20by%20Nicholas%20Roerich%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20younger%20son%2C%20Svetoslav%2C%20often%20more%20famous%20as%20the%20husband%20of%20Devika%20Rani%2C%20the%20First%20Lady%20of%20Indian%20cinema%2C%20also%20did%20his%20bit%20through%20his%20numerous%20paintings.%20He%20remained%20in%20India%20all%20his%20life.%20%C2%A0%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThere's%20another%20legacy%20Roerich%20has%20left%20behind%3A%20the%20Roerich%20Pact%2C%20or%20the%20Treaty%20on%20the%20Protection%20of%20Artistic%20and%20Scientific%20Institutions%20and%20Historic%20Monuments.%20An%20international%20legal%20document%2C%20the%20pact%20is%20aimed%20at%20ensuring%20the%20unconditional%20protection%20of%20cultural%20property.%20The%20pact%20has%20never%20been%20more%20significant%20than%20today%20as%20the%20world%20witnesses%20the%20wilful%20destruction%20of%20ancient%20and%20cultural%20heritage%20in%20places%20like%20Afghanistan%2C%20Iraq%2C%20Syria%2C%20and%20Gaza.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20Is%20No%20Future%20Without%20The%20Past%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Roerich%2C%20knowledge%20and%20beauty%20epitomised%20life%20itself.%20This%20sentiment%20is%20beautifully%20portrayed%20in%20his%20drama%20%3Cem%3EMercy%20%3C%2Fem%3E('Miloserdiye')%20which%20this%20writer%20has%20been%20privileged%20to%20have%20translated%20from%20Russian%20to%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoerich%20passed%20away%20on%20December%2015%2C%201947.%20In%20keeping%20with%20indic%20tradition%2C%20Nicholas%2C%20his%20wife%20and%20later%20son%20Svetoslav%2C%20were%20all%20cremated%20and%20samadhis%20erected%20over%20their%20ashes.%20His%C2%A0demise%20put%20an%20end%20to%20the%20work%20of%20the%20Urusvati%20Centre%3B%20it%20is%20now%20a%20museum%20of%20the%20International%20Roerich%20Memorial%20Trust%2C%20which%20houses%20a%20number%20of%20paintings%20by%20both%20Roerich%20and%20son%20Svetoslav.%20Yet%2C%20his%20rich%20legacy%20remains%20almost%20obscure%20in%20India%2C%20restricted%20to%20niche%20circles.%20This%20Russian%20friend%20of%20India%20deserves%20far%20more.%20As%20Roerich%20said%3A%20there%20is%20no%20future%20without%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Aditi%20Bhaduri%20is%20a%20journalist%20and%20political%20analyst.%20She%20has%20translated%20the%20works%20of%20Nicholas%20Roerich%20from%20Russian%20to%20English)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728459720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2F6rnt4e1o_roerich_625x300_09_October_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fremembering-nicholas-roerich-the-russian-who-made-kullu-his-home-6750202%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nicholas%20Roerich%2C%20who%20was%20born%20on%20this%20day%20150%20years%20ago%2C%20was%20first%20and%20foremost%20an%20Indophile%2C%20someone%20who%20perhaps%20can%20be%20said%20to%20have%20laid%20the%20foundation%20of%20Indo-Russian%20friendship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fremembering-nicholas-roerich-the-russian-who-made-kullu-his-home-6750202%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22RBI%20MPC%3A%20Short-term%20inflation%20risk%20remains%20in%20focus%2C%20says%20Shaktikanta%20Das%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728459711000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-09%2F10%2Fthumb%2Ffitandfill%2F400X400%2F1725952519-0477.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Frbi-mpc-short-term-inflation-risk-remains-in-focus-says-shaktikanta-das-124100900457_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20press%20statement%20after%20the%20RBI's%20Monetary%20Policy%20announcement%2C%20RBI%20Governor%20Shaktikanta%20Das%20said%20the%20inflation%20worries%20have%20eased%20but%20there%20is%20a%20need%20for%20greater%20vigilance%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Frbi-mpc-short-term-inflation-risk-remains-in-focus-says-shaktikanta-das-124100900457_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-stan