C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CA%20home%20is%20a%20place%20where%20you%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20loved%20and%20cared%20for.%20Children%20in%20such%20families%20are%20also%20affected%20as%20they%20are%20silent%20witnesses%20to%20the%20crime.%20Growing%20up%2C%20they%20assume%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20normal%20life%20is%20about.%20When%20such%20kids%20date%20or%20are%20in%20live-in%20relationships%2C%20they%20express%20love%20and%20anger%20in%20ways%20they%20learn%20from%20their%20own%20homes%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Prasanna.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20family%20must%20take%20responsibility%20%E2%80%94%20in%20how%20we%20communicate%20at%20home%2C%20how%20we%20raise%20our%20children%2C%20and%20how%20we%20ensure%20equality%20in%20the%20upbringing%20of%20both%20girls%20and%20boys.%20The%20way%20parents%20argue%20and%20shout%20in%20front%20of%20children%20matters.%20Otherwise%2C%20this%20behaviour%20risks%20becoming%20an%20intergenerational%20cycle%20of%20violence%2C%20where%20children%20grow%20up%20to%20become%20perpetrators%20themselves.%20We%20need%20to%20break%20this%20cycle%2C%E2%80%9D%20Prasanna%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Teach%20children%20about%20respectful%20relationships%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20highlights%20the%20importance%20of%20education%20in%20combating%20domestic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20certain%20attitude%20that%20normalises%20violence.%20To%20change%20it%2C%20we%20must%20focus%20on%20education%2C%E2%80%9D%20Prasanna%20says.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSchools%20can%20play%20a%20very%20big%20role%20in%20educating%20kids%20about%20respectful%20relationships%20through%20specially%20designed%20programmes.%20Schools%20can%20also%20help%20